於[[希臘神話|希臘神話]]中, [[雅典娜|雅典娜]]與[[波塞冬|波塞冬]]爭奪[[雅典|雅典城]]。波塞冬以三叉戟插在[[雅典衛城|雅典衛城]]上以示主權，使一井噴出海水。雅典娜則於井旁種首棵橄欖樹回應。眾神法殿裁定後者更有權得此地，因其予以之禮物更佳。<ref>Robert Graves, ''The Greek Myths'', Penguin, 1960, Sect.16.c</ref>橄欖枝為當時新娘所戴<ref name="OED">"Olive branch". ''The Oxford English Dictionary'', online ed., 2004. [http://dictionary.oed.com/cgi/entry/00331258?single=1&query_type=word&queryword=olive+branch&first=1&max_to_show=10] (subscription required)</ref>，亦作為禮物賜予當時[[奧運會|奧運會]]的觀眾。<ref name="Penn">{{Cite web |url=http://www.museum.upenn.edu/new/olympics/olympicfaqs.shtml |title=The Real Story of the Ancient Olympic Games<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2009-06-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090603045335/http://www.museum.upenn.edu/new/olympics/olympicfaqs.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>

橄欖枝曾是[[厄瑞涅|厄瑞涅]]於古羅馬錢幣上的一個特徵(attribute)<ref name=theoi>{{Cite web |url=http://www.theoi.com/Ouranios/HoraEirene.html |title=''Theoi Greek Mythology'' |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2016-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121070831/http://www.theoi.com/Ouranios/HoraEirene.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=c7cNB-JaZA8C&pg=PT64&dq=eirene+%2B%22olive+branch%22&hl=en&ei=eeTHTaizIs2LswbfvK3JDw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CEAQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=eirene%20%2B%22olive%20branch%22&f=false |title=Kathleen N. Daly and Marian Rengel, ''Greek and Roman Mythology A to Z'', New York: Chelsea House, 2009 |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2013-10-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131003050342/http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=c7cNB-JaZA8C&pg=PT64&dq=eirene++%22olive+branch%22&hl=en&ei=eeTHTaizIs2LswbfvK3JDw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CEAQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=eirene%20%2B%22olive%20branch%22&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.coinsofromanegypt.org/html/library/bmc_intro/html%20files/coinage_2.html |title=Coins of Roman Egypt |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2012-03-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313060140/http://www.coinsofromanegypt.org/html/library/bmc_intro/html%20files/coinage_2.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>例如公元七十到七一年的一個[[維斯帕先|維斯帕先]][[四德拉克馬銀幣|四德拉克馬銀幣]]，就展示企立的厄瑞涅，右手握著倒轉的橄欖枝。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.beastcoins.com/Collections/KeithEmmettEgypt/C0334.jpg |title=Keith Emmett Collection of Roman Egypt |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2016-11-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161125043338/http://www.beastcoins.com/Collections/KeithEmmettEgypt/C0334.jpg |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[羅馬|羅馬]]詩人[[維吉爾|維吉爾]](公元前七零至一零年) 以「豐滿的橄欖」<ref>Virgil, ''Georgics'', 2, pp.425ff (trans. Fairclough)</ref>喻[[帕克斯|帕斯]]女神 (羅馬文化中的厄瑞涅<ref name=theoi/>)，並以於詩作《[[埃涅阿斯紀|埃涅阿斯紀]]》中以橄欖作喻和平的像徵 <ref name=greatseal>[http://www.greatseal.com/peace/olivebranchvirgil.html Great Seal]</ref>

:高艉之上，立埃涅阿斯
:雙手所持，一撮橄欖枝
:道：如爾所見，弗里吉亚之大軍 
:於特洛依遭逐，在意大利被挑
:為拉丁仇敵所困，陷於不義之戰
:始以結盟，終以背叛 
:今以此信物告天下：特洛依人及其首領
:願結和平，求王饒恕

對羅馬人而言，戰爭與和平，兩者關係密切。[[瑪爾斯|瑪爾斯]]有戰神之名，卻同時有「安慰者」之稱，乃和平使者。後期羅馬帝國的錢幣上，就顯示其手執橄欖枝的模樣。<ref>Ragnar Hedlund, "Coinage and authority in the Roman empire, c. AD 260–295", ''Studia Numismatica Upsaliensia'', 5, University of Uppsala, 2008</ref><ref name=elmes/>羅馬史學家[[阿皮安|阿皮安]]，於記述[[努曼廷戰爭|努曼廷戰爭]]時，提到羅馬將軍[[小西庇阿|小西庇阿]]使用橄欖枝作為和平的象徵。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.livius.org/ap-ark/appian/appian_spain_19.html#1 |title=Appian's History of Rome: The Spanish Wars (§§91-95) |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2012-01-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120113152510/http://www.livius.org/ap-ark/appian/appian_spain_19.html#1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[迦太基|迦太基]]的[[哈斯德魯巴_(馬西尼薩外孫)|哈斯德魯巴·博埃薩爾克]]亦如是記載。<ref>[[Nathaniel_Hooke|Nathaniel Hooke]], [http://books.google.com/books?id=Qu3QAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA58&lpg=PA58&dq=olive+branch+roman+surrender&source=bl&ots=OwdxfognYq&sig=_u8M1Pl-JKR7xklKHxtajN23bSY&hl=en&ei=XDDdTIHTM5OahQeJ3-HGDQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=9&ved=0CEsQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=olive-branch&f=false ''The Roman history: From the Building of Rome to the Ruin of the Commonwealth,'' London:  J. Rivington, 1823] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Qu3QAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA58&lpg=PA58&dq=olive+branch+roman+surrender&source=bl&ots=OwdxfognYq&sig=_u8M1Pl-JKR7xklKHxtajN23bSY&hl=en&ei=XDDdTIHTM5OahQeJ3-HGDQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=9&ved=0CEsQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=olive-branch&f=false |date=20140625191803 }}</ref>雖然於古希臘時代，橄欖枝就與和平有所聯繫，此象徵在[[羅馬治世|羅馬治世]]時更為強烈，因使節多以橄欖枝喻和平。<ref>Tresidder, Jack, ed. The Complete Dictionary of Symbols. San Francisco: Chronicle, 2004.</ref>

==初代基督教時期==
早期[[基督教|基督教]]藝術品中，已有橄欖枝與白鴿之出現。白鴿源自[[福音書|福音書]]中[[聖靈|聖靈]]的借喻，橄欖枝則為古老符號之傳承。根據[[約翰·約阿希姆·溫克爾曼|溫克爾曼]]記載，初代基督徒之墓室，常有口啣橄欖枝之白鴿，以明其和平無爭之志。<ref name=elmes>{{Cite web |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=iSWGTy2WeVsC&pg=PT472&lpg=PT472&dq=pacifer+%2Bolive&source=bl&ots=knWZF7ELCR&sig=RgPVlfMRdnTqGbt_FIzGlUwgSJw&hl=en&ei=tE6kTLfWNZG7jAeb6ZCoDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CCYQ6AEwBQ#v=snippet&q=olive%20branch&f=false |title=James Elmes, ''A General and Bibliographical Dictionary of the Fine Arts'', London: [[Thomas_Tegg|Thomas Tegg]], 1826 |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2020-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801032933/https://books.google.com/books?id=iSWGTy2WeVsC&pg=PT472&lpg=PT472&dq=pacifer+%2Bolive&source=bl&ots=knWZF7ELCR&sig=RgPVlfMRdnTqGbt_FIzGlUwgSJw&hl=en&ei=tE6kTLfWNZG7jAeb6ZCoDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CCYQ6AEwBQ#v=snippet&q=olive%20branch&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>例如位於羅馬的[[殉道者墓窟|佩西位墓窟]](公元二至五世紀), 其上展示三個男人，及一啣欖枝白鴿於天空盤旋(一般認為三人組是[[但以理書|但以理書]]中的[[沙得拉，米煞，亞伯尼歌|沙得拉，米煞，亞伯尼歌]]<ref>[http://www.santamelania.it/preg_lett/orante/orante.htm Parrochia di Santa Melania] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100929163655/http://www.santamelania.it/preg_lett/orante/orante.htm |date=2010-09-29 }}</ref>)。於另一羅馬墓窟中，有一浮雕展示飛翔白鴿口啣欖枝，飛向以希臘文標注為「和平」(ΕΙΡΗΝΗ)的人像<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.salomoni.it/davide/theology/blog/images/catacomb_dove.png |title=David Salmoni |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2012-03-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314122557/http://www.salomoni.it/davide/theology/blog/images/catacomb_dove.png |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[特土良|特土良]](公元一六零至二二零年)就白鴿的形像，以希伯萊聖經及浸信會之神靈說的作比較。前者「於方舟而出，並啣欖枝而回，向世界宣告聖怒之消退。」後者則「從天堂而來，予人神賜平安。」<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=zkvl7ZwGQhMC&q=dove#v=snippet&q=dove&f=false |title=Hall, Christopher A., ''Worshipping with the Church Fathers'', InerVarsity Press, 2009, p.32 |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2014-01-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140102013617/http://books.google.com/books?id=zkvl7ZwGQhMC&q=dove#v=snippet&q=dove&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[耶柔米|聖耶柔米]]於公元四世紀，將挪亞的事跡譯成拉丁文。其中「橄欖葉」(希伯萊文''alay zayit'')，於其翻譯的[[創世紀|創世紀]]中，成了「橄欖枝」(拉丁文''ramum olivae'')。於公元五世紀，白鴿與欖枝已成為象徵和平的基督教符號。[[希波的奧古斯丁|聖奥古斯丁]]於其著作[[論基督教教義|論基督教教義]]，寫道「白鴿帶回方舟之橄欖枝(''oleae ramusculo'')，代表永恆之和平。」但猶太傳統中，橄欖枝並未出現於洪水之故事，故其亦無與和平之聯繫。<ref name=greatseal/><ref>''[[Genesis_Rabbah|Genesis Rabbah]]'', 33:6</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.halakhah.com/sanhedrin/sanhedrin_108.html#PARTb |title=Babylonian Talmud Sanhedrin 108b |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2012-02-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120203130401/http://www.halakhah.com/sanhedrin/sanhedrin_108.html#PARTb |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.halakhah.com/pdf/moed/Eiruvin.pdf |title=Eruvin 18b |access-date=2013-09-29 |archive-date=2018-11-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181120043935/http://www.halakhah.com/pdf/moed/Eiruvin.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==現代用途==
十八世紀之英國及美國，白鴿配橄欖枝已成為和平的象徵。一七七一年，其時[[北卡羅萊納州|北卡羅萊納州]]之兩英磅鈔票上，就印有白鴿橄欖枝，並有短題「回復和平」。一七七八年[[喬治亞州|喬治亞州]]的四十美元鈔票上，則有白鴿橄欖枝，以及持短刀之手，短題為「戰爭和平，皆有所備」<ref name=greatseal/>同時期之印制品亦見此符號。一七七五年一月，倫敦雜誌的卷首頁就印有「有雲從商業之殿來，和平自雲降臨」，並展示和平女神予英美兩國橄欖枝。一七七五年七月，為避免與大英帝國全面開戰，美國[[大陆会议|大陸國會]]發起了請願，其名正正為「橄欖枝請願」。<ref name=greatseal/>

一七七六年七月四日(即美國十三州退離英國獨立之日)，美國通過決議案，批准創造[[美国国徽|美國官方大紋章]]，亦即[[美國國徽|美國國徽]]。現今國徽有一禿鷹以右爪執橄欖枝，左爪執箭，但這並不是最初的設計。第一設計委員會的作品並沒有兩者，要到第二設計委員會橄欖枝才出現。其上的十三塊葉片象徵最初獨立的十三州。及後的委員會及人任逐漸加入禿鷹及其他元素，形成現今之形象。橄欖枝與箭的對比，是為了「顯示國會選擇和平或戰爭的專屬權力」。<ref>Charles Thomson as referred to in <The Great Seal of the United States. Washington D.C.: U.S. Department of State Bureau of Public Affairs, 2003.</ref>

橄欖枝之意義亦見於[[阿拉伯世界|阿拉伯地區]]。<ref>{{cite book|title=Folk traditions of the Arab world: a guide to motif classification, Volume 1|url=https://archive.org/details/folktraditionsof0001elsh|author= Hasan M. El-Shamy|publisher=[[Indiana_University_Press|Indiana University Press]]|year=1995|page=[https://archive.org/details/folktraditionsof0001elsh/page/410 410]}}</ref>一九七四年，[[巴勒斯坦|巴勒斯坦]]領袖[[亚西尔·阿拉法特|阿拉法特]]手持橄欖枝，到聯合國總部演說：「今日我來，帶著橄欖枝與自由戰士的槍。不要使我的橄欖枝掉下。」<ref>{{cite news|title=Mahmoud Abbas: haunted by ghost of Yasser Arafat|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/palestinianauthority/8784000/Mahmoud-Abbas-haunted-by-ghost-of-Yasser-Arafat.html|location=London|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=23 September 2011|accessdate=2013-09-29|archive-date=2021-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210717055133/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/palestinianauthority/8784000/Mahmoud-Abbas-haunted-by-ghost-of-Yasser-Arafat.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>而联合国徽章与旗帜中也有橄榄枝图案。

